  "body": "...because it's awesome.\r\n\r\n### Proposed Functionality\r\n\r\n#### Deployment Interaction:\r\n- [x] query a registry for an ABI and contract address, and returns a [`Contract`](https://eth-brownie.readthedocs.io/en/latest/api-network.html#brownie.network.contract.Contract) object\r\n- [x] query a registry and generate a [`Project`](https://eth-brownie.readthedocs.io/en/latest/api-project.html#project) from the entire manifest, including `Contract` objects for deployed contracts\r\n\r\n#### Registry Interaction:\r\n- [x] list all known registries\r\n- [ ] list all packages in a registry\r\n- [ ] search a registry for a package / version\r\n- [x] list locally available packages\r\n\r\n#### Project integration:\r\n- [x] add packages to a project via `brownie ethpm install [uri]`\r\n  - store package source code inside a project's `contracts/` directory\r\n  - track installed packages in `build/packages.json`, warn the user loudly when source in an installed package has been modified\r\n- [x] generate and publish a package from a project\r\n- [ ] allow references to installed package by name/alias\r\n\r\n#### Bonus points:\r\n- [x] re-introduce deployment persistence (#246)\r\n- [ ] create a Brownie registry: `pm.eth-brownie.eth`\r\n- [ ] create a test registry on Roptsen\r\n\r\n### Useful Links\r\n* [official documentation](https://docs.ethpm.com/)\r\n* [EthPM Package Manifest Documentation](https://ethpm.github.io/ethpm-spec/index.html)\r\n* [original EIP spec](https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/issues/190)\r\n* `web3.py`: [package manager](https://web3py.readthedocs.io/en/stable/web3.pm.html) / [ethPM](https://web3py.readthedocs.io/en/stable/ethpm.html)\r\n* [how Truffle did it](https://www.trufflesuite.com/docs/truffle/getting-started/package-management-via-ethpm)\r\n* [Dai manifest that includes dependencies](http://explorer.ethpm.com/manifest/Qmd4xvKG8cKFDMCYdzgbGN5rf98VfP4bYwqArPQ7mdyEwf)",
